This product includes software and derives from the following projects:

1. anthropics/jacobian-lens (Apache License 2.0)
   The reference Jacobian-lens implementation and the paper
   "Verbalizable Representations Form a Global Workspace in Language Models".
   Used via the fork github.com/fblissjr/jacobian-lens.
   Lens apply semantics, the chain convention (J_{l-1} = J_l . M_l), and the
   fit corpus/position handling derive from this work.

2. WeZZard/jlens-qwen36 (Apache License 2.0)
   MLX on-device fitting for the qwen3_5 (Gated-DeltaNet hybrid) architecture:
   the custom Metal GDN backward kernel and the analytic branch-Jacobian
   assembly. The contents of vendor/jlens_qwen36/ are copied verbatim from this
   project as a porting seed; modifications are tracked as they are modularized
   into jlens_mlx/ (see MIGRATION.md). Per-file provenance headers name the
   origin.

3. Neuronpedia (MIT) — design inspiration only, no code.
   The production interp platform (neuronpedia.org/jlens). The model-agnostic
   provider posture, the customizable-corpus stance, the layer-range navigation,
   and the steer/swap/ablate intervention design informed this project's
   direction. No Neuronpedia code is included.

Each vendored file retains its upstream copyright and license notice.
